# Agentor Rules

Agentor is an agent execution runtime, not a knowledge-state engine.

Keep these boundaries:

- Agentor executes agents, steps, tools, policies, traces, and manifests.
- Athanor remains the canonical knowledge-state service.
- Conexus remains the LLM/model gateway.
- MCP integration comes later.

PR1 scope is deliberately small:

- deterministic fake run only
- no LLM calls
- no Athanor runtime call
- no Conexus runtime call
- no MCP
- no vector store
- no background jobs
- no dashboard

Do not add new abstractions unless they are used by PR1 tests.

Every tool call must have a PolicyDecision.
Every run must emit ExecutionTraceEvent items.
Every completed run must produce a RunManifest.
